About Me

Hello, I am Mitch Hoesing.


As of July 2021, I am an automation developer at Intel, via the contracting company UST. On the side I work on projects which include this website and an artificial intelligent research project that I am unable to write too much on for bias reasons.

I have a couple of goals currently. Number one is to get myself into an artificial intelligence role. My plan to achieve this involves going back to graduate school to provide myself with more time to study AI. After graduating with a Master's Degree, I will apply to positions that allow me to continue learning to become an artificial intelligence consultant for businesses. I believe there is a large market for businesses that can operate more efficiently with the use of AI and I want to provide that service. Goal number two is to own real estate and other cash flowing assets. I will finance these investments with my AI background and in time retire with assets to live from.

My hobbies include disc golfing, programming, running & weight lifting, reading, video gaming, garage sales, cooking, meditating, photography, art, biking and fishing.
